{
  "title": "Personalized Search Ranking at Etsy: Leveraging User Interactions and Contextual Features",
  "summary": "Etsy has implemented a personalized search ranking system that leverages user interactions and contextual features to improve the relevance of search results. By analyzing user behavior such as clicks, favorites, add-to-carts, and purchases, Etsy has developed a robust model that enhances the user experience and increases conversion rates.",
  "key_points": [
    {
      "section": "User Interactions as Signals",
      "content": "User interactions such as clicks, favorites, add-to-carts, and purchases are used as signals to understand user preferences. Clicks are the most frequent and provide a rich source of data, while purchases are less frequent but indicate stronger relevance."
    },
    {
      "section": "Contextual Features for Personalization",
      "content": "Etsy uses three types of contextual features for personalization: Tf-Idf vectors, interaction-based graph embeddings, and item-interaction vectors. These features capture the textual and behavioral context of user interactions with listings."
    },
    {
      "section": "Item-Interaction Vectors",
      "content": "Item-interaction vectors are created by replacing words and sentences with item-interaction token pairs. These vectors capture the sequence of user interactions and allow for the identification of similar listings based on shared interaction patterns."
    },
    {
      "section": "Personalized Search Ranking",
      "content": "In personalized search ranking, user contextual features are combined with historical features and non-personalized features to train a decision tree. This tree learns how each feature impacts the likelihood of a purchase and ranks items accordingly."
    },
    {
      "section": "Performance Evaluation",
      "content": "Online A/B experiments showed that personalized search results improved ranking performance, as measured by normalized discounted cumulative gain (NDCG). Users found what they wanted faster, clicked less, and bought more items with the personalized variant."
    },
    {
      "section": "Challenges and Considerations",
      "content": "Personalized search results introduce latency challenges due to the need to rank listings for every user and query pair. Additionally, privacy considerations must be taken into account, such as anonymizing personalization data and respecting user preferences."
    }
  ],
  "conclusion": "Etsy's personalized search ranking system demonstrates the power of leveraging user interactions and contextual features to improve the relevance of search results. By continuously refining the model and addressing challenges such as latency and privacy, Etsy enhances the user experience and drives better business outcomes."
}

